The paper deals with Markov decision processes (MDPs) and their complexity in enforcing constraints on multi-dimensional weighted MDPs. This involves analyzing systems with multiple objectives that may be conflicting and require the analysis of trade-offs. The paper also considers classical quantitative payoffs from the literature. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as MDPs are commonly used in modeling multi-agent systems. The paper also deals with algorithms and strategies, which suggests a likelihood of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of quantitative payoffs and probability thresholds suggests a likelihood of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) respectively. Finally, the analysis of trade-offs and constraints suggests a likelihood of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
